WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.127
[sighs]

00:02.210 --> 00:05.547
Welcome to Eleven O'Clock.
My name is Greta.

00:05.630 --> 00:07.048
[Caterina] Allegra?

00:07.132 --> 00:08.758
-Mom, I--
-We're going home. "Mom," nothing.

00:08.842 --> 00:11.386
I want to be "Ellie," the lead in
<i>Freaky Friday</i>, just like Grandma.

00:11.469 --> 00:14.097
I don't want to hear you talk
about Cocó ever again.

00:14.180 --> 00:15.181
-Mom!
-[glass shatters]

00:15.265 --> 00:16.266
PREVIOUSLY

00:16.349 --> 00:17.851
[Allegra] <i>Grandma. Thank you for coming.</i>

00:17.934 --> 00:19.978
<i>I wish I could change what happened.</i>

00:21.604 --> 00:23.940
-[gasps]
-[Cocó] Caterina. Stop dillydallying.

00:24.024 --> 00:26.401
-That's my specialty.
-[whispering] Mom?

00:26.484 --> 00:28.194
-I have to stop by the video store.
-Cocó?

00:29.029 --> 00:30.238
Laura. Where did you go?

00:30.321 --> 00:31.156
LAURA ISN'T HERE

00:31.239 --> 00:32.824
[chuckles] Sorry. I have to go.

00:33.950 --> 00:35.702
Are you planning to stand there all day?

00:35.785 --> 00:37.495
-Greta?
-Do we know each other?

00:37.579 --> 00:39.247
[Greta] Hey, babe.

00:40.832 --> 00:42.500
[Cocó] <i>You can't let her win.</i>

00:42.584 --> 00:44.586
The role of "Ellie" has to be yours.

00:44.669 --> 00:46.338
<i>Don't let me down.</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:50.550
-[Allegra] Did you hurt yourself?
-No, it was just a bump.

00:50.633 --> 00:52.093
I can't believe you're here.

00:54.596 --> 00:55.805
Who are you?

01:00.060 --> 01:01.311
Who are you?

01:01.394 --> 01:04.189
If-- If I tell you,
you'll think I'm crazy.

01:04.272 --> 01:05.690
I need you to listen to me.

01:05.774 --> 01:09.069
You don't know how important it is
for me to be here with you.

01:09.694 --> 01:11.279
-Security!
-No, no, no. [shushes]

01:11.363 --> 01:13.531
-Security!
-[groans]

01:16.242 --> 01:18.411
What's going on? Hey! Come here.

01:18.495 --> 01:20.497
COMING SOON

01:29.923 --> 01:31.549
Galleria
CAMDEN

01:32.592 --> 01:35.136
[guard] Hey, stop running!

01:35.220 --> 01:36.388
[grunts, pants]

01:40.642 --> 01:42.769
[panting]

01:50.527 --> 01:51.695
[guard] Hey! Hey!

01:54.364 --> 01:55.699
Stop! Stop running!

02:09.004 --> 02:10.463
[groans]

02:12.424 --> 02:13.675
[sighs]

02:20.640 --> 02:22.600
[panting]

02:27.605 --> 02:28.606
[gasps]

02:38.533 --> 02:40.535
[dial tone]

02:51.379 --> 02:53.840
INTERTWINED

02:55.258 --> 02:57.260
[rumbling]

02:57.344 --> 02:58.678
[groans]

03:07.187 --> 03:09.189
[sirens wailing]

03:30.251 --> 03:31.336
Excuse me!

03:32.087 --> 03:33.713
[chuckles] Where are we?

03:35.632 --> 03:37.842
We're on planet Earth.

03:37.926 --> 03:39.386
[chuckles] No. What day is it?

03:40.303 --> 03:41.554
-Today.
-Of what year?

03:41.638 --> 03:42.806
2021.

03:45.975 --> 03:48.687
Do you have any other… questions?

03:54.150 --> 03:55.902
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

03:57.612 --> 04:00.615
[Cocó] Good morning. Allegra?

04:02.617 --> 04:03.952
Are you up?

04:47.620 --> 04:49.289
[female assistant] Thirty-seven.

04:50.248 --> 04:53.752
Sixty-three. Twenty-two.

04:53.835 --> 04:55.837
[chattering]

04:57.130 --> 04:58.214
Seventy-eight.

05:01.176 --> 05:02.177
Seventy-nine.

05:04.471 --> 05:05.513
Ninety-four.

05:09.184 --> 05:10.352
Allegra Sharp?

05:10.435 --> 05:11.770
[crowd murmuring]

05:11.853 --> 05:12.854
Allegra?

05:13.813 --> 05:15.648
-[girl] No, she didn't come.
-Seven.

05:15.732 --> 05:18.068
[chuckles] Obviously
she wasn't going to come

05:18.151 --> 05:20.028
after what happened at the first audition.

05:20.111 --> 05:22.572
-The Sharps made quite a scene.
-[assistant] Forty-two.

05:22.655 --> 05:25.825
Like your mom always says,
don't air your dirty laundry in public.

05:25.909 --> 05:26.993
[assistant] Twenty-six.

05:27.077 --> 05:28.745
That's my mom's specialty.

05:30.038 --> 05:31.164
I need to concentrate.

05:31.790 --> 05:34.042
-You're the best. Relax.
-[assistant] Thirteen.

05:34.125 --> 05:36.086
What? Do I look nervous?

05:37.921 --> 05:39.172
-No, no.
-[assistant] Twenty-six.

05:42.050 --> 05:43.718
[vital signs monitor beeping]

05:43.802 --> 05:45.679
[Allegra] I don't even know
where to start.

05:47.639 --> 05:50.433
Why did you never tell me
you were a part of Eleven O'Clock?

05:54.604 --> 05:56.022
She just opened her eyes!

05:56.106 --> 05:57.816
[door opens]

05:58.608 --> 06:01.069
Okay. Excuse me, I have to examine her.

06:01.152 --> 06:02.987
But I don't understand.
She was just awake.

06:03.071 --> 06:06.825
Yes. That's normal in these cases.
But don't worry. She's in the clear now.

06:06.908 --> 06:09.661
On top of that, it's surprising how much
she improved overnight.

06:10.787 --> 06:14.165
I told you that your mother was
a strong woman. She always has been.

06:20.672 --> 06:22.298
Shouldn't you be at the theater?

06:23.299 --> 06:24.342
What theater?

06:24.426 --> 06:26.011
Eleven O'Clock. The vocal audition.

06:27.262 --> 06:28.304
How did you know?

06:33.476 --> 06:36.479
It doesn't make sense.
Mom will never sign the permission slip.

06:36.563 --> 06:38.148
There's always a way.

06:38.231 --> 06:41.151
You just get ready for the audition.
I'll take care of the rest.

06:41.234 --> 06:42.527
[nurse speaking Spanish]

06:42.610 --> 06:45.572
Your mom will be fine. And you can't
miss out on this opportunity.

06:48.825 --> 06:53.204
♪ <i>I've been ignoring my heart</i>
<i>For so long</i> ♪

06:53.288 --> 06:58.209
♪ <i>It beats but it's mechanical</i> ♪

06:59.044 --> 07:03.798
♪ <i>I worked so hard</i>
<i>To control the situation</i> ♪

07:03.882 --> 07:09.262
♪ <i>And now I feel a chaos that's better</i> ♪

07:09.346 --> 07:14.017
♪ <i>If the fear is something I made up</i>
<i>Now I know there's another way</i> ♪

07:14.100 --> 07:19.397
♪ <i>To starve the monster</i>
<i>That strikes fear</i> ♪

07:19.481 --> 07:24.444
♪ <i>Today the fear disappears</i> ♪

07:24.527 --> 07:28.073
♪ <i>I leap without fear</i> ♪

07:28.156 --> 07:29.657
♪ <i>There's no turning back</i> ♪

07:31.368 --> 07:32.660
[sighs]

07:34.287 --> 07:37.123
[Allegra] And I met my great-grandmother,
who was my grandmother's age,

07:37.207 --> 07:39.417
and my grandmother was my mom's age.

07:39.501 --> 07:41.169
And my mom was my age!

07:41.252 --> 07:43.463
Wow. Insane. I can't believe it.

07:43.546 --> 07:46.216
To me, Caterina was born 40 years old.

07:46.299 --> 07:47.926
No, and she was a whole other person.

07:48.009 --> 07:50.637
She was fun, sure of herself--

07:50.720 --> 07:53.473
Zero bad vibes.
And everything was different.

07:53.556 --> 07:56.893
Okay, okay. Let's say this is real, okay?
How did you get there?

07:58.895 --> 08:00.855
It all started when I put on
this bracelet.

08:04.776 --> 08:07.237
[Diego] Well, how do I say this?

08:07.320 --> 08:12.659
Um, it was very good. Very polished.
You have a very beautiful voice.

08:13.576 --> 08:18.123
The only thing was
in the lead-in to the chorus.

08:18.206 --> 08:22.711
Your voice was shaky, and I think that
minor detail hindered your performance.

08:22.794 --> 08:24.462
But it was very, very good.

08:25.797 --> 08:26.965
[male judge] Sofía,

08:27.048 --> 08:30.927
a good performer cannot let themself
be carried away by their emotions.

08:31.011 --> 08:35.640
For me, the shaky voice
is not minor at all.

08:35.724 --> 08:37.851
To me, it spoiled your audition.

08:37.934 --> 08:39.644
[crowd murmurs]

08:39.728 --> 08:43.481
All right. It's true that her voice
was a little shaky,

08:43.565 --> 08:47.277
but I think that what she conveyed
was very strong.

08:48.153 --> 08:50.363
To me, the performance was very good.

08:50.447 --> 08:54.159
Besides, it's an audition.
Nerves are to be expected.

08:54.826 --> 08:56.453
Thank you, Sofía.

08:57.245 --> 08:58.621
Next, please.

09:02.250 --> 09:03.918
[horns honking]

09:04.002 --> 09:08.673
Wow. I've read about hallucinations,
but I didn't think they were that vivid.

09:08.757 --> 09:10.425
Clearly, it was the shock
from the accident.

09:10.508 --> 09:11.843
-You don't get it, Félix.
-[sighs]

09:11.926 --> 09:14.846
They weren't hallucinations.
My mom was at Eleven O'Clock!

09:14.929 --> 09:18.767
If your mom was a performer
at the company, I'm Peter Jackson.

09:19.893 --> 09:22.937
-He's a film director. Orcs, the ring--
-Look!

09:26.733 --> 09:28.651
[Félix] "Cocó Sharp's Successor."

09:28.735 --> 09:29.986
FAME

09:31.363 --> 09:33.490
-Why didn't she ever tell me? Mmm?
-Uh…

09:33.573 --> 09:36.076
I don't know, Allegra.
This is crazy. This is totally crazy.

09:36.159 --> 09:39.537
Didn't you hear her?
She said she saw it with her own eyes!

09:39.621 --> 09:40.914
-Thank you!
-You're welcome.

09:40.997 --> 09:44.834
Sir, could you focus on driving, please?
We're running late.

09:44.918 --> 09:47.337
[horns honking]

09:47.420 --> 09:49.881
And I can't stop thinking about
the fight we had.

09:49.964 --> 09:52.842
If we hadn't been arguing,
we would've never gotten in that crash--

09:52.926 --> 09:55.762
No, no. Look, it's not your fault, okay?

09:56.471 --> 09:58.932
I always thought Mom and I
were so different, but I don't know.

09:59.766 --> 10:01.267
Maybe I was wrong.

10:02.686 --> 10:07.440
[sighs] You should've seen her
on stage, Félix. She was incredible.

10:08.066 --> 10:10.068
-[Félix clicks tongue]
-[bracelet whooshing]

10:13.196 --> 10:15.031
-Did you see what I just saw?
-What's going on?

10:15.115 --> 10:16.741
Yes. I see a blocked road. I see traffic.

10:16.825 --> 10:18.910
-I see that we're getting nowhere.
-No. I'm serious, Félix.

10:18.993 --> 10:21.371
-A knot in the bracelet just came untied.
-By itself?

10:21.454 --> 10:22.455
[chuckles]

10:23.289 --> 10:25.166
You're in worse condition than I thought.

10:25.250 --> 10:27.293
I-- I am being serious. You're… Ugh.

10:27.377 --> 10:29.212
Sir, I think we'll get out here.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.172
-Hey!
-I already paid through the app, okay?

10:31.256 --> 10:33.258
[horns honking]

10:37.637 --> 10:39.639
[Allegra panting]

10:45.353 --> 10:46.354
You're late.

10:52.360 --> 10:53.862
Wait! Please!

10:54.612 --> 10:55.780
Allegra.

10:55.864 --> 10:57.991
[Allegra] I'm sorry.
I couldn't get here any sooner.

10:58.074 --> 11:01.244
We're not interested in excuses.
You should've been on time.

11:01.327 --> 11:03.329
Can't you make an exception?

11:03.413 --> 11:05.498
In my company,
we don't make exceptions for anyone.

11:06.207 --> 11:09.044
And I find it strange that your mom
changed her mind so quickly

11:09.127 --> 11:12.297
after the scene she made
at the last audition.

11:12.380 --> 11:14.049
Her mom was in an accident.

11:14.132 --> 11:15.342
How? What happened to Caterina?

11:15.425 --> 11:18.762
We got in a car accident,
and she is in the hospital.

11:18.845 --> 11:20.847
-What?
-But she's out of the woods now.

11:20.930 --> 11:22.974
She's still in the hospital though.

11:23.058 --> 11:26.186
I am so sorry. I really am.

11:26.269 --> 11:29.564
But without her permission,
you can't try out.

11:29.647 --> 11:31.316
I think these are
exceptional circumstances.

11:31.399 --> 11:34.402
Maybe we should consider
giving her another chance?

11:34.486 --> 11:38.156
No, Diego. She had her chance,
and she didn't show up.

11:38.239 --> 11:40.950
I'm really sorry
about your mother, but no, no.

11:41.618 --> 11:42.869
I agree with Greta.

11:47.374 --> 11:48.541
[sighs]

11:48.625 --> 11:50.627
[heart beating]

11:53.630 --> 11:54.923
♪ <i>Oh, God</i> ♪

11:55.006 --> 11:59.844
♪ <i>How could I have been so afraid</i> ♪

12:00.595 --> 12:04.641
♪ <i>And not have thought</i>
<i>That fear can suffocate you</i> ♪

12:04.724 --> 12:05.725
♪ <i>Mmm</i> ♪

12:05.809 --> 12:07.143
[crowd murmurs]

12:07.227 --> 12:12.148
♪ <i>Everything I've faced was hard</i> ♪

12:12.232 --> 12:15.902
♪ <i>And now, how do I fix it?</i> ♪

12:15.985 --> 12:17.404
[music playing on speaker]

12:17.487 --> 12:22.701
♪ <i>I can't promise you</i>
<i>That this world will change</i> ♪

12:22.784 --> 12:27.831
♪ <i>But I can assure you</i> ♪

12:27.914 --> 12:32.836
♪ <i>Today the fear disappears</i> ♪

12:32.919 --> 12:37.757
♪ <i>No more being afraid of being afraid</i>
<i>I will walk with you</i> ♪

12:37.841 --> 12:43.304
♪ <i>With no sadness or pain</i> ♪

12:43.388 --> 12:48.435
♪ <i>Unstoppable from today on</i> ♪

12:48.518 --> 12:50.520
-[music stops playing]
-[Allegra sighs]

12:51.104 --> 12:53.314
-[Félix cheering]
-[applause, cheering]

12:53.398 --> 12:54.983
-[man] Bravo!
-[woman] Incredible.

12:55.066 --> 12:56.901
-[woman] Awesome.
-[man] Beautiful.

13:01.322 --> 13:03.033
That was…

13:03.116 --> 13:06.369
Wow. You're just like your grandmother.

13:06.453 --> 13:10.165
Just like Cocó. A little less hair spray
on your head, but…

13:10.248 --> 13:15.503
We're looking for the best possible cast.
Allegra is undoubtedly an amazing singer.

13:15.587 --> 13:17.839
But she doesn't have
her mother's permission.

13:21.092 --> 13:23.970
[Cocó] I can sign her permission slip.

13:25.638 --> 13:29.851
[in English] OMG. Cocó Sharp is here.

13:29.934 --> 13:32.896
-I've died and gone to heaven, eh?
-Thanks, dear. That's enough.

13:32.979 --> 13:35.982
Cocó. What are you doing here?

13:36.608 --> 13:39.110
I'm here on behalf of Caterina.

13:39.194 --> 13:42.989
While she's in the hospital,
I'm Allegra's guardian.

13:43.073 --> 13:45.367
Caterina didn't want
her daughter to audition.

13:45.450 --> 13:48.078
Don't worry.
I'll make sure she signs everything.

13:48.161 --> 13:49.788
Once she's discharged, of course.

13:49.871 --> 13:51.081
Perfect. It's all sorted.

13:51.164 --> 13:55.251
No. We don't play favorites here.
The rules are clear.

13:55.335 --> 13:56.753
Come on, Greta.

13:56.836 --> 14:00.131
You're telling me you never broke
the rules to get what you wanted?

14:05.345 --> 14:06.596
[chuckles]

14:06.680 --> 14:07.681
Okay.

14:07.764 --> 14:08.807
[sighs]

14:08.890 --> 14:11.226
[Greta] Congratulations, Allegra.

14:11.309 --> 14:12.811
You're in luck.

14:12.894 --> 14:14.104
There's lots of time

14:14.187 --> 14:16.398
-before the last audition.
-Ooh. [giggles]

14:16.481 --> 14:19.109
Let's see if you can convince Caterina.

14:22.696 --> 14:23.947
[chuckles]

14:24.030 --> 14:26.032
-[crowd murmurs]
-[man] Unbelievable.

14:27.534 --> 14:28.785
Ah! [giggles]

14:30.495 --> 14:32.497
Magic Ink

14:34.541 --> 14:36.543
CONTEMPORARY DANCE

14:38.211 --> 14:40.213
I don't know
if it's Caterina Sharp's genes

14:40.296 --> 14:42.132
or a tsunami that passed
through your room.

14:42.215 --> 14:44.551
[chuckles] No, neither.

14:44.634 --> 14:49.764
It's just-- I left in a hurry,
and I didn't know what to wear.

14:52.517 --> 14:55.937
Thank you. Without your help,
I would never have passed the audition.

14:56.021 --> 14:57.939
You have nothing to thank me for.

14:58.023 --> 15:00.400
You are a diamond in the rough.

15:01.276 --> 15:04.362
But with my help, you will become
a great performer.

15:04.446 --> 15:06.114
I'm sure of it.

15:06.197 --> 15:07.949
[chuckles]

15:09.701 --> 15:11.202
Who are your instructors?

15:11.286 --> 15:14.706
Maybe I know them.
And we can work together.

15:14.789 --> 15:16.541
[Allegra] Uh…

15:16.624 --> 15:18.418
-Tutorials.
-What?

15:19.711 --> 15:22.756
I taught myself watching videos
on the Internet.

15:22.839 --> 15:27.302
Mom never let me take classes.
Not voice, not dance, not acting.

15:28.345 --> 15:29.679
You inherited my dedication.

15:29.763 --> 15:32.098
[chuckles] And hopefully your talent.

15:32.182 --> 15:38.772
Ha. Talent is worthless without effort,
hard work and discipline.

15:40.482 --> 15:44.027
Eleven O'Clock was always known
for one thing:

15:44.110 --> 15:46.571
the tenacity of its performers.

15:46.654 --> 15:50.825
[sighs] I can't even imagine what it would
feel like to be a part of Eleven O'Clock.

15:51.743 --> 15:53.953
Words can't describe it.

15:54.662 --> 15:57.791
It would be like trying to describe dance.

15:59.417 --> 16:03.755
If I could tell you how it feels,
then dancing wouldn't be worth it.

16:06.591 --> 16:08.510
What was my mom like at my age?

16:08.593 --> 16:10.220
[sighs]

16:10.303 --> 16:14.140
She was always falling asleep.
She was always late to everything.

16:15.016 --> 16:16.184
To Eleven O'Clock?

16:17.185 --> 16:19.187
How did you know she was
a part of the company?

16:20.522 --> 16:21.856
Did she tell you?

16:21.940 --> 16:24.150
[sighs] No, she never wanted
to talk about it,

16:24.234 --> 16:26.695
-but I found this.
-[phone beeps]

16:30.740 --> 16:32.534
Why didn't she stay with the company?

16:35.286 --> 16:37.831
Cocó, please. I need to know
what happened between you two.

16:37.914 --> 16:39.874
It's so hard to explain.

16:41.084 --> 16:45.922
The decisions your mom made
had consequences for everyone.

16:47.173 --> 16:49.968
Don't let the shadows of the past
dim your future,

16:50.844 --> 16:54.222
which I am certain is bright.

16:54.305 --> 16:57.392
It's better to leave the past in the past.

17:03.273 --> 17:07.777
♪ <i>Unstoppable from today on</i> ♪

17:10.864 --> 17:13.783
What's up? Watching your favorite actress?

17:14.576 --> 17:15.577
[sighs]

17:16.703 --> 17:20.498
The other day, I saw a movie
that reminded me of you and Allegra.

17:20.582 --> 17:22.250
No, no, no. Come on, come on.

17:22.334 --> 17:25.962
The main character wanted to win over
his best friend.

17:26.046 --> 17:28.006
But because he spends
all his time watching movies,

17:28.089 --> 17:29.591
he obviously knows nothing about girls.

17:30.633 --> 17:33.011
So he asks his older brother,
who's good with the ladies…

17:33.094 --> 17:34.846
-[scoffs]
-…and muscular, for help--

17:34.929 --> 17:36.890
Shouldn't you be studying? Mmm?

17:36.973 --> 17:39.768
You failed seven subjects--
Or no, was it eight?

17:39.851 --> 17:42.270
-Seven. Eight.
-[scoffs]

17:42.354 --> 17:44.689
And so what?
Shouldn't you be working on your short?

17:44.773 --> 17:46.524
No longer interested
in that film scholarship?

17:46.608 --> 17:49.486
For your information,
I already wrote the script.

17:49.569 --> 17:52.364
Why aren't you filming then?
Your girl doesn't have time for you?

17:52.447 --> 17:54.240
This is my issue. Mine alone.

17:54.324 --> 17:59.120
I understand this is difficult to
get through your thick head-- Clearly.

17:59.204 --> 18:02.332
But for the millionth time,
Allegra is not my girlfriend.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.000
She's my friend. Understood?

18:04.084 --> 18:08.088
She's your friend, but if she were more,
you wouldn't complain. [chuckles]

18:08.171 --> 18:09.756
-Can I give you some advice?
-No, no.

18:09.839 --> 18:13.218
I'm going to give it to you anyway.
I think that…

18:13.301 --> 18:15.553
I think Allegra is manipulative.

18:15.637 --> 18:16.888
[scoffs]

18:16.971 --> 18:18.723
Didn't you see how she played
the grandma card

18:18.807 --> 18:20.225
to move up in the company, Félix?

18:20.308 --> 18:21.685
Uh, no. Okay. You're wrong.

18:21.768 --> 18:24.396
Allegra doesn't need to play any cards.

18:24.479 --> 18:25.814
Her talent speaks for itself.

18:25.897 --> 18:27.899
[phone ringing]

18:30.360 --> 18:31.820
Don't leave her waiting.

18:31.903 --> 18:32.946
[clicks tongue] Go.

18:34.239 --> 18:35.240
Allegra.

18:37.117 --> 18:38.576
[Félix groans]

18:39.494 --> 18:42.706
[sighs] What if we tried
with pruning shears? That'll work.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.333
I told you it won't come off.
I've tried a thousand times.

18:45.417 --> 18:46.501
[sighs]

18:46.584 --> 18:49.421
I have news. You won't believe
what I found out about the past.

18:49.504 --> 18:51.881
All of this is totally insane.
Totally insane.

18:52.882 --> 18:55.510
-Okay, what did you find out? Tell me.
-No, no, no.

18:55.593 --> 18:56.594
-[scoffs]
-Look.

18:57.762 --> 19:00.473
It's an article about
the <i>Freaky Friday</i> tour in '94.

19:00.557 --> 19:03.560
But Greta was the lead. Her plan worked.

19:03.643 --> 19:04.853
Her plan?

19:04.936 --> 19:07.981
I heard Greta say that my mom
was on borrowed time.

19:08.064 --> 19:09.399
Don't you get it, Félix?

19:09.482 --> 19:13.111
My mom could have been
a musical theater star,

19:13.194 --> 19:14.696
but Greta stole her chance.

19:15.613 --> 19:18.658
[sighs] That's why she doesn't even want
to talk about Eleven O'Clock.

19:18.742 --> 19:21.369
The life she's living now is her plan B,
not her dream.

19:21.453 --> 19:26.916
[scoffs] Good interpretation, really.
Excellent.

19:27.000 --> 19:28.251
With just one little thing. Mmm.

19:28.335 --> 19:31.087
And it's that your mom seems
pretty happy with the life she has.

19:31.171 --> 19:32.297
No. You're wrong.

19:32.380 --> 19:33.798
So, what are you going to do?

19:35.300 --> 19:37.552
-I have to go back and change the past.
-[scoffs]

19:37.635 --> 19:40.889
Yes, I have to get into the company
and stop Greta from bringing my mom down.

19:40.972 --> 19:43.391
[clears throat] Don't you think
this plan is a little ambitious?

19:43.475 --> 19:47.979
No. If my mom is the lead on opening day,
she'll be Ellie for the whole season.

19:48.063 --> 19:50.690
And that will make her
Cocó Sharp's successor.

19:50.774 --> 19:52.484
And the three of us will be together.

19:52.567 --> 19:53.777
-Allegra, wait.
-No, no, no.

19:53.860 --> 19:57.197
I'm sure the relationship between my mom
and my grandma could get better.

19:58.073 --> 19:59.407
And everything will change.

19:59.491 --> 20:03.119
My mom will sign the permission slip.
I need your help.

20:03.203 --> 20:05.663
My help? With what?

20:05.747 --> 20:08.500
[sighs] To go back to the past.

20:08.583 --> 20:11.044
[upbeat music playing]

20:11.127 --> 20:11.961
TAKE 1

20:19.761 --> 20:21.388
TAKE 2

20:24.015 --> 20:25.308
TAKE 4

20:29.187 --> 20:30.355
TAKE 8

20:35.610 --> 20:37.320
TAKE 10

20:45.745 --> 20:46.746
TAKE 22

20:51.042 --> 20:53.253
TAKE 53

21:09.644 --> 21:10.895
[music ends]

21:11.896 --> 21:14.274
I told you. You were hallucinating.

21:14.357 --> 21:18.194
We tried all the possible combinations,
and nothing worked.

21:19.320 --> 21:20.405
[sighs]

21:21.406 --> 21:24.325
Come on. Let's think
about something else. For a bit.

21:25.326 --> 21:28.329
Like… I don't know, the sky.

21:28.955 --> 21:31.416
-Look at the night sky. It's… perfect.
-Perfect.

21:33.418 --> 21:34.419
[both chuckle]

21:35.295 --> 21:40.842
The stars too.
They're… starrier than ever.

21:42.844 --> 21:45.013
[chuckles] I'm glad you're here.

21:45.889 --> 21:47.891
[Félix sighs] Mmm.

21:55.482 --> 21:58.610
Allegra. I need to tell you something.

21:59.611 --> 22:02.781
So, company is important, right?

22:02.864 --> 22:04.240
No, not Eleven O'Clock.

22:04.324 --> 22:06.034
-Eleven O'Clock is…
-[music playing on phone]

22:06.117 --> 22:07.243
…an important company, right?

22:07.327 --> 22:09.329
-A musical theater company.
-[bracelet ringing]

22:12.165 --> 22:14.084
I'm talking about company--
The company you keep.

22:14.167 --> 22:16.628
-With you, I'm in good company. Well…
-Félix!

22:18.380 --> 22:19.589
Félix!

22:19.673 --> 22:21.216
[gasps]

22:23.009 --> 22:24.010
What should I do?

22:34.729 --> 22:35.730
[gasps]

22:36.481 --> 22:38.066
[music continues on phone]

22:38.149 --> 22:40.151
-[panting]
-[dog barking]

22:41.945 --> 22:47.659
♪ <i>You never know about a battle</i> ♪

22:54.791 --> 22:55.792
[Allegra groans]

22:56.793 --> 22:57.836
Ouch.

22:59.337 --> 23:00.338
[groans]

23:02.841 --> 23:03.925
Are you all right?

23:08.221 --> 23:09.305
Yes. Yes.

23:09.389 --> 23:14.102
Uh, um, I-- I tripped on your flowers.
Sorry, Lucía.

23:15.562 --> 23:17.939
What are you doing in my garden?
Do we know each other?

23:20.275 --> 23:24.904
Caterina told me… [groans]
…to come around back.

23:24.988 --> 23:27.657
Yes. So I wouldn't wake her mother.

23:27.741 --> 23:30.869
Oh! You're a friend of Caterina's.

23:31.578 --> 23:33.621
That must be why your face looks familiar.

23:33.705 --> 23:35.248
No, Caterina went to rehearsal.

23:35.957 --> 23:37.959
And Cocó? I need to speak with her.

23:38.043 --> 23:39.669
She went to the theater too,
with Caterina.

23:39.753 --> 23:43.798
-Of course, because I should be there too.
-Hmm.

23:43.882 --> 23:46.092
I'll get out of your way.
Sorry about your flowers.

23:46.176 --> 23:47.218
No, don't worry about it.

23:47.302 --> 23:49.596
Flowers are a lot stronger
than they appear.

23:49.679 --> 23:53.475
Sometimes you need a good fall
to get up stronger, right?

23:53.558 --> 23:54.684
[chuckles]

23:54.768 --> 23:56.895
You can grab Caterina's bicycle
if you want.

23:56.978 --> 23:58.855
All right. Thanks. See you.

24:26.675 --> 24:29.344
-Sorry, sorry, sorry. You can go now.
-No, Mom. It's all right. Yes.

24:29.427 --> 24:31.096
-You'll make it. Don't worry.
-Bye.

24:37.686 --> 24:40.438
♪ <i>Are you listening?</i>
<i>On your mark</i> ♪

24:40.522 --> 24:43.108
♪ <i>And don't fall behind</i> ♪

24:43.858 --> 24:46.528
♪ <i>And if you learn to look</i> ♪

24:46.611 --> 24:49.906
♪ <i>The unexpected may occur</i> ♪

24:49.989 --> 24:53.243
♪ <i>There will be hurdles to jump</i> ♪

24:53.326 --> 24:56.121
♪ <i>Many rocks to dodge</i> ♪

24:56.204 --> 24:59.082
♪ <i>You can't finish without starting</i> ♪

24:59.165 --> 25:00.792
Ah! [clears throat]

25:00.875 --> 25:04.254
♪ <i>Your desire and your resolution</i> ♪

25:04.337 --> 25:10.802
♪ <i>Will collide</i> ♪

25:10.885 --> 25:13.888
♪ <i>I'm going to decide what I want to be</i> ♪

25:13.972 --> 25:16.766
♪ <i>Who I want to be</i> ♪

25:16.850 --> 25:20.979
♪ <i>Maybe I'm almost there</i> ♪

25:21.062 --> 25:24.941
♪ <i>Maybe</i> ♪

25:27.986 --> 25:29.738
Five, six, seven, eight…

25:31.614 --> 25:33.783
[applause, cheering]

25:33.867 --> 25:36.161
[Cocó] Good. Quiet, quiet.

25:36.244 --> 25:38.913
Save the applause
for when you actually deserve it, mmm?

25:44.419 --> 25:46.171
[mumbling]

25:49.549 --> 25:50.884
[in English] Good morning.

26:04.230 --> 26:05.231
[chuckles]

26:06.566 --> 26:08.568
[continues mumbling]

26:11.529 --> 26:12.530
Mmm.

26:15.408 --> 26:16.576
Eight, nine…

26:18.078 --> 26:19.079
[Cocó] <i>Good.</i>

26:19.996 --> 26:24.668
As you know, we still need to determine
who will play Ellie on opening day.

26:25.502 --> 26:28.171
I'll make a decision
after the next dress rehearsal.

26:29.214 --> 26:32.175
-First, we're going to watch Greta.
-[giggles]

26:32.258 --> 26:35.720
And then following with the same number,
Caterina.

26:36.638 --> 26:38.223
We're done for today.

26:39.974 --> 26:40.975
Greta!

26:42.602 --> 26:44.813
Don't let it happen again.
Lateness will not be tolerated.

26:44.896 --> 26:45.897
No, actually I--

26:45.980 --> 26:48.525
On top of that, you didn't warm up.
You could have hurt yourself.

26:52.195 --> 26:53.196
[sighs]

26:58.785 --> 26:59.911
Nobody understands me.

27:00.954 --> 27:02.622
What's going on, Cocó?
Why do you say that?

27:02.706 --> 27:06.918
It's practically the same stage design
as when I played Ellie.

27:08.044 --> 27:11.506
I need something that lives up to
the Eleven O'Clock company's reputation.

27:12.215 --> 27:15.635
-With all due respect, Cocó. That--
-Do you have a dictionary in your house?

27:15.719 --> 27:16.845
Yes. Why?

27:16.928 --> 27:20.015
Why don't you look up
the meaning of the word "innovation"?

27:20.098 --> 27:22.142
It's clear you have no idea
what I'm talking about.

27:22.225 --> 27:23.893
-Uh, Cocó?
-Tomás.

27:24.936 --> 27:28.648
If you stopped playing with those things
you have there for just a second

27:28.732 --> 27:32.110
and paid attention to what is
happening here, you'd agree with me.

27:32.193 --> 27:34.154
First of all, this isn't a thing.

27:34.237 --> 27:37.240
It's a very valuable work of art
I just brought back from Paris.

27:37.323 --> 27:41.619
Secondly, I think we can continue, uh,
working on this proposal

27:42.495 --> 27:45.707
in order to achieve
what we're all looking for, right?

27:46.916 --> 27:48.626
It won't be ready for opening day.

27:48.710 --> 27:50.670
That is not
an acceptable response, Camilo.

27:50.754 --> 27:52.756
If you need more people, hire them.

27:53.673 --> 27:58.178
But I need a better proposal.
Is that clear?

27:58.928 --> 28:00.096
All right.

28:00.180 --> 28:05.018
You'll have a new proposal by tomorrow,
but it will change the budget.

28:05.101 --> 28:07.187
All right.
When did I say money was an issue?

28:07.270 --> 28:08.605
-No.
-Go ahead.

28:09.314 --> 28:10.315
If you'll excuse me.

28:14.361 --> 28:16.488
-Don't worry, Cocó.
-Ugh, Tomás…

28:16.571 --> 28:17.739
Don't worry.

28:17.822 --> 28:22.077
I promise to invest whatever it takes

28:22.160 --> 28:27.499
to make sure <i>Freaky Friday</i> is
the hit musical of the season.

28:27.582 --> 28:29.042
I swear to it.

28:29.125 --> 28:30.335
[both chuckle]

28:30.418 --> 28:31.753
[piano playing]

28:38.093 --> 28:41.930
♪ <i>Na, na, na, na</i> ♪

28:42.013 --> 28:45.225
♪ <i>Na, na, na, na, na, na, na</i> ♪

28:46.267 --> 28:49.312
♪ <i>Na, na, na, na</i> ♪

28:49.938 --> 28:53.149
♪ <i>Na, na, na, na, na, na, na</i> ♪

28:53.900 --> 28:57.320
♪ <i>Na, na, na, na</i> ♪

28:57.946 --> 29:01.616
♪ <i>Na, na, na, na, na, na, na</i> ♪

29:05.704 --> 29:08.206
So? What do you think?

29:08.289 --> 29:09.290
Well…

29:10.417 --> 29:12.335
I shouldn't have played it for you.

29:12.419 --> 29:14.671
-It's not done yet, but I thought that--
-[laughs]

29:14.754 --> 29:16.506
Oh, okay.

29:16.589 --> 29:19.175
Not only is it not that great,
it's funny too. Fantastic.

29:19.259 --> 29:20.719
-[Caterina] Ugh.
-[scoffs]

29:20.802 --> 29:24.764
Someone needs to learn
to manage their expectations.

29:24.848 --> 29:28.810
And I have just the cure for that.

29:28.893 --> 29:33.064
One season at the Sharp residence,
and you'll be immune to all criticism.

29:33.148 --> 29:34.566
[both chuckle]

29:34.649 --> 29:36.776
I think I'd prefer for you
to keep critiquing me.

29:40.947 --> 29:42.157
I loved it.

29:42.240 --> 29:43.825
-Really? You liked it?
-Mm-hmm.

29:44.659 --> 29:47.912
I hear it, and thousands of images
come to mind.

29:49.039 --> 29:51.374
Well, since you liked it so much,

29:51.458 --> 29:53.960
you can help me with the lyrics,
if you want.

29:54.044 --> 29:56.921
If you give me the recording on cassette,
I'll start writing today.

29:58.506 --> 29:59.966
No. No, no, please. Not here.

30:00.050 --> 30:03.303
If Cocó sees me, she'll kick me
out of the company in a heartbeat.

30:03.386 --> 30:04.637
Cocó won't find out.

30:06.014 --> 30:08.016
-[door opens]
-[grunts]

30:08.099 --> 30:09.517
-[footsteps approaching]
-[gasps]

30:09.601 --> 30:12.437
[Cocó] I don't know. I don't know.
I don't know what's going on.

30:21.321 --> 30:24.908
-Um. Uh… Diego was playing--
-Yes.

30:24.991 --> 30:27.369
-Was playing me a song--
-A song.

30:27.452 --> 30:29.412
I think the only song
you should be thinking about

30:29.496 --> 30:31.998
is the one you need to have ready
for the dress rehearsal.

30:32.665 --> 30:34.292
You made some mistakes today.

30:34.918 --> 30:36.378
I know you haven't been practicing.

30:36.461 --> 30:39.047
I-- I was leaving, eh.

30:39.130 --> 30:41.132
I'll leave you the-- the cassette.

30:41.758 --> 30:43.593
Uh… [breathes heavily]

30:43.677 --> 30:45.095
[footsteps departing]

30:45.178 --> 30:47.597
-Caterina.
-Mom, please don't start.

30:47.681 --> 30:49.724
-I will practice later.
-Now.

30:49.808 --> 30:52.686
Or do you want Greta to get the part
of Ellie on opening day?

30:57.649 --> 30:59.901
[Greta] <i>If it were broken,</i>
<i>I'd be crying, Bárbara.</i>

30:59.984 --> 31:01.194
It's a sprain at most.

31:01.277 --> 31:04.322
Oh, you think that's nothing?
You have to see a doctor.

31:04.406 --> 31:05.407
Well, not now.

31:05.490 --> 31:08.535
If Cocó finds out, she's going to
take the lead from me on opening day.

31:08.618 --> 31:11.204
[scoffs] She's going to take the lead
from you anyway, sweetie.

31:11.287 --> 31:12.872
Yes, Tomás told me so.

31:12.956 --> 31:15.959
And he also told me that the stage design
has these spinning panels--

31:16.042 --> 31:17.794
-Who cares about the stage design?
-Mmm.

31:17.877 --> 31:19.754
What did he tell you about Caterina?

31:19.838 --> 31:21.881
What we already know, sweetie.

31:21.965 --> 31:24.968
Cocó has already decided to give her
the role of Ellie on opening day.

31:25.885 --> 31:26.886
[sighs]

31:27.595 --> 31:31.224
I think the time has come to kick-start
my plan to get Caterina out of my way.

31:32.267 --> 31:36.021
You're going to come before
the dress rehearsal for "It's Biological."

31:36.104 --> 31:38.148
-Me?
-Yes, you.

31:38.898 --> 31:41.985
And you'll loosen the trapdoor
on the stage

31:42.068 --> 31:44.571
where Caterina ends her choreography.

31:46.990 --> 31:49.617
Isn't that… too much?

31:51.119 --> 31:56.958
If I have to choose between my future
and Caterina's,

31:57.042 --> 31:59.085
I think you already know my choice.

32:03.048 --> 32:04.883
I can't do it without you.

32:08.511 --> 32:10.638
[sighs] Okay. Okay.

32:13.391 --> 32:14.392
Ow.

32:16.436 --> 32:17.896
[Bárbara] Do you want a hand?

32:17.979 --> 32:19.064
[Greta groans]

32:19.147 --> 32:20.148
[gasps]

32:24.194 --> 32:26.654
[Bárbara] But what if Caterina
can never dance again?

32:26.738 --> 32:29.032
[Greta] Don't blow this out of proportion.

32:29.115 --> 32:31.201
She'll be out for a season at most.

32:41.461 --> 32:46.132
♪ <i>I've been ignoring my heart</i>
<i>For so long</i> ♪

32:46.216 --> 32:50.303
♪ <i>It beats</i>
<i>But it's mechanical</i> ♪

32:51.346 --> 32:56.726
♪ <i>I worked so hard</i>
<i>To control the situation</i> ♪

32:56.810 --> 33:01.648
♪ <i>And now I feel a chaos that's better</i> ♪

33:01.731 --> 33:06.736
♪ <i>If the fear is something I made up</i>
<i>Now I know there's another way</i> ♪

33:06.820 --> 33:11.032
♪ <i>To starve the monster</i>
<i>That strikes fear</i> ♪

33:11.825 --> 33:16.496
[both] ♪ <i>Today the fear disappears</i> ♪

33:17.122 --> 33:20.709
♪ <i>I leap without fear</i> ♪

33:20.792 --> 33:22.669
[both] ♪ <i>There's no turning back</i> ♪

33:25.630 --> 33:26.715
♪ <i>Oh, God</i> ♪

33:26.798 --> 33:32.012
♪ <i>How could I be so afraid</i>
<i>And not have thought</i> ♪

33:32.095 --> 33:35.765
♪ <i>That fear can suffocate you</i> ♪

33:37.142 --> 33:42.397
♪ <i>Everything I've faced was hard</i> ♪

33:42.480 --> 33:45.900
♪ <i>And now, how do I fix it?</i> ♪

33:47.777 --> 33:52.824
♪ <i>I can't promise you</i>
<i>That this world will change</i> ♪

33:52.907 --> 33:57.454
[both] ♪ <i>But I can assure you</i> ♪

33:57.537 --> 34:02.167
♪ <i>Today the fear disappears</i> ♪

34:02.876 --> 34:05.879
♪ <i>No more being afraid of being afraid</i> ♪

34:05.962 --> 34:08.089
♪ <i>I will walk with you</i> ♪

34:08.173 --> 34:12.677
[both] ♪ <i>With no sadness or pain</i> ♪

34:13.636 --> 34:15.889
♪ <i>Unstoppable</i> ♪

34:15.972 --> 34:18.350
[both] ♪ <i>From today on</i> ♪

34:22.479 --> 34:23.813
[guard] Hey!

34:23.897 --> 34:26.733
This time you won't get away.
You can't be here. Let's go.

34:26.816 --> 34:28.651
-Let go of me.
-Let go. You're going to hurt her.

34:28.735 --> 34:31.154
-Stay out of this. Get out of here!
-[Cocó] What's going on?

34:31.237 --> 34:32.906
This girl is trespassing.

34:32.989 --> 34:35.408
This girl has a name. Her name is Laura.

34:35.492 --> 34:37.869
[crowd murmuring]

34:40.372 --> 34:42.040
What is Marco doing here?

34:42.916 --> 34:46.920
And she could change once in a while,
am I right? [giggles]

34:47.003 --> 34:48.546
I just want to join the company.

34:48.630 --> 34:51.007
Auditions are over. Please escort her out.

34:51.091 --> 34:52.884
-[guard] Of course.
-[Caterina] You!

34:54.302 --> 34:56.137
-What are you doing here?
-[Cocó] Do you know her?

34:56.221 --> 34:58.139
It's the girl I told you about.
The one who hugged me.

34:58.223 --> 35:01.017
I'm here because it's my dream to be
a part of an Eleven O'Clock production.

35:01.101 --> 35:02.644
All I ask for is a chance.

35:02.727 --> 35:05.855
All you're asking for is not possible.
The cast is set.

35:05.939 --> 35:08.942
Please, I love <i>Freaky Friday</i>.
I know it by heart, and I know--

35:09.025 --> 35:10.944
Oh, oh, oh. What are you going to tell me?

35:11.027 --> 35:14.739
That your talent is incomparable?
That you're unique? Everyone says that.

35:14.823 --> 35:18.076
The auditions for this musical are over.
It'll have to be the next one.

35:21.830 --> 35:25.166
I can't tell you how important it is to me
to be a part of Eleven O'Clock.

35:25.250 --> 35:26.960
It's like dance.

35:27.043 --> 35:31.840
If I could explain to you how it feels,
then dancing wouldn't be worth it, right?

35:33.258 --> 35:34.342
[scoffs]

35:35.719 --> 35:38.138
-All right. Let's go. Please leave.
-Give me a second.

35:53.069 --> 35:54.070
Well, all right.

35:55.113 --> 35:57.824
Let's see if it's true that you know
the musical by heart.

35:57.907 --> 35:58.908
-[gasps]
-What?

36:00.702 --> 36:02.162
She's auditioning?

36:02.245 --> 36:04.205
She can't. There are no more parts.

36:04.289 --> 36:07.208
Everyone is replaceable, Greta.
Don't forget that.

36:09.085 --> 36:10.170
Off the stage, please.

36:16.301 --> 36:19.346
You shouldn't have any problem
performing Ellie.

36:20.472 --> 36:21.848
I'll play Katherine.

36:25.727 --> 36:26.728
[sighs]

36:50.377 --> 36:53.505
♪ <i>It's not time to talk</i>
